1 packet Chargrilled Capsicum Relish
250 g Beef & Pork Mince
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 Celery
1 packet Baby Leaves
1 packet Garlic Aioli
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 sachet Chermoula Spice Blend
1 packet Garlic Paste
1 drizzle olive oil
1 tsp honey
1 drizzle white wine vinegar

• Thinly slice celery.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat.
• Cook beef & pork mince, breaking up with a spoon, until browned,3-4 minutes.
• Add chermoula spice blend and garlic paste and cook, stirring until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Remove from heat, then add the honey and toss to combine. Season to taste.

• Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, combine shredded cabbage mix, celery, baby leaves and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil. Season with salt and pepper.
• Microwave mini flourtortillas on a plate in 10 second bursts, until warmed through.

• Spread chargrilled capsicum relish over tortillas, then top with celery slaw and Middle Eastern-spiced beef and pork.
• Drizzle over garlic aioli to serve. Enjoy!